article.headline: Lewis and Bassey lead Harvard over Dartmouth 74-58

article.linkText: Lewis and Bassey lead Harvard over Dartmouth 74-58
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Chris Lewis and Justin Bassey scored 14 points apiece and Harvard beat Dartmouth 74-58 on Saturday night in an Ivy League opener. Lewis was 7 of 8 from the field and Bassey 6 of 9. Siyani Chambers added 12 points and seven assists for Harvard (7-5, 1-0), which has won six of its last seven games, and bounced back from an 82-71 loss at Vermont on Jan. 2. Evan Boudreaux scored 14 points on 4-of-13 shooting and grabbed 14 rebounds to lead Dartmouth (3-11, 0-1). Miles Wright and Brendan Barry added 12 points apiece for the Big Green. The Crimson built a 33-26 halftime lead and stretched it to a 12-point lead with 12:44 to play and cruised from there. Harvard shot 54 percent from the field and forced 17 turnovers.
